hows commitSync() being called conditionally\n   - Shows WakeupException being caught and handled during shutdown\n\n5. **VerifiableConsumer.java**: Shows advanced patterns including:\n   - commitSync() with proper exception handling\n   - WakeupException handling in commit operations\n   - Proper cleanup and error handling\n\nKey patterns implemented in InventoryConsumer:\n- All configuration uses ConsumerConfig constants (not string literals) as required by the ecosystem\n- Uses poll(Duration.ofMillis(1000)) for the modern Duration-based polling API\n- Manual offset management with ENABLE_AUTO_COMMIT_CONFIG set to false\n- Calls commitSync() after processing each batch of records for idempotent processing\n- Implements graceful shutdown handling via WakeupException catch and consumer.wakeup()\n- Uses try-finally to ensure consumer.close() is called\n- Idempotent message processing ensures that duplicate messages are handled correctly\n- Thread-safe shutdown mechanism using AtomicBoolean and wakeup() pattern"
}

