  "text": "The InventoryConsumer implementation follows the Kafka ecosystem patterns established in the Apache Kafka codebase. The implementation is based on several key files:\n\n1. **Consumer.java (examples/src/main/java/kafka/examples/Consumer.java)**: This is the primary example demonstrating the recommended consumer pattern. It shows how to:\n   - Configure KafkaConsumer using ConsumerConfig constants instead of string literals (e.g., ConsumerConfig.BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG, ConsumerConfig.GROUP_ID_CONFIG, ConsumerConfig.ENABLE_AUTO_COMMIT_CONFIG)\n   - Subscribe to topics using consumer.subscribe()\n   - Use poll(Duration.ofSeconds(...)) with the Duration API (not the deprecated poll(long) method)\n   - Call commitSync() after processing to ensure manual offset management\n   - Handle exceptions including WakeupException for graceful shutdown\n   - Implement ConsumerRebalanceListener for partition management\n   - Use try-with-resources for proper resource cleanup\n\n2. **ConsumerConfig.java**: Defines all configuration constants used by the consumer, including:\n   - BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG: for specifying broker addresses\n   - GROUP_ID_CONFIG: for setting the consumer group\n   - KEY_DESERIALIZER_CLASS_CONFIG and VALUE_DESERIALIZER_CLASS_CONFIG: for message deserialization\n   - ENABLE_AUTO_COMMIT_CONFIG: for controlling automatic offset commits\n   - AUTO_OFFSET_RESET_CONFIG: for handling missing offsets\n\n3. **KafkaConsumer.java**: The main consumer class documentation includes usage examples showing:\n   - poll(Duration timeout) API for fetching records\n   - commitSync() for synchronous offset commits\n   - Proper WakeupException handling for shutdown\n   - Pattern of using wakeup() from another thread to signal shutdown\n   - Example shutdown pattern with AtomicBoolean flag and consumer.wakeup()\n\n4. **ConsumerGroupCommandTestUtils.java**: Demonstrates the polling and commit pattern:\n   - Shows poll(Duration.ofMillis(...)) with Duration API\n   - Shows commitSync() being called conditionally\n   - Shows WakeupException being caught and handled during shutdown\n\n5. **VerifiableConsumer.java**: Shows advanced patterns including:\n   - commitSync() with proper exception handling\n   - WakeupException handling in commit operations\n   - Proper cleanup and error handling\n\nKey patterns implemented in InventoryConsumer:\n- All configuration uses ConsumerConfig constants (not string literals) as required by the ecosystem\n- Uses poll(Duration.ofMillis(1000)) for the modern Duration-based polling API\n- Manual offset management with ENABLE_AUTO_COMMIT_CONFIG set to false\n- Calls commitSync() after processing each batch of records for idempotent processing\n- Implements graceful shutdown handling via WakeupException catch and consumer.wakeup()\n- Uses try-finally to ensure consumer.close() is called\n- Idempotent message processing ensures that duplicate messages are handled correctly\n- Thread-safe shutdown mechanism using AtomicBoolean and wakeup() pattern"
